<item>
            <title>[SPARK-15914] Add deprecated method back to SQLContext for source code backward compatiblity</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-15914</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We removed some deprecated method in SQLContext in branch Spark 2.0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;  @deprecated(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Use read.json(). This will be removed in Spark 2.0.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;1.4.0&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
  def jsonFile(path: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;): DataFrame = {
    read.json(path)
  }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These deprecated method may be used by existing third party data source. We probably want to add them back to remain source code level backward compatibility. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
